laboratory_examinations.findings: Liver is fatty infiltrated with an area of sparing in the right lobe.
Mild fat stranding surrounding the appendix; colonic diverticulosis with no evidence of acute diverticulitis.
Mildly hyperdense material in the gallbladder may represent small gallstones.
Uterus, urinary bladder and rectum appear unremarkable; left ovary contains multiple small cysts, likely physiologic.
